meanings.definition: To climb faster or higher than someone or something else.
meanings.sent1: The squirrel outclimbs the cat to reach the top of the tree.
meanings.sent2: She always outclimbs her friends when they go hiking.
meanings.sent3: The spider challenged the ant to a race, confident it could outclimb its tiny competitor.
meanings.sent4: The determined mountaineer outclimbs all obstacles to conquer the summit.
meanings.sent5: The agile monkey effortlessly outclimbs its competitors in the jungle.

meanings.sent1: The young athlete outclimbs his older brother in rock climbing.
meanings.sent2: The experienced climber always outclimbs the newcomers at the gym.
meanings.sent3: The spider outclimbs the snail, leaving it far behind on the wall.
meanings.sent4: Her determination to outclimb her fears led her to the top of the mountain.
meanings.sent5: The mountain goat outclimbs all other animals with its sure-footed agility.
